-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/THIR> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasRockUnitRank> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/RockUnitRank/U> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ACTV> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "300m approx."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/AOL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "About 3 to 21m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ASLS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Type section up to about 6.45m. Maximum c.22m (Cleeve Hill area)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ASY> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.140m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BAGP> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Averages c.1800m."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BDS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "To c.120m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BEAS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Thicknesses quoted by authors for the same localities may be at considerable variance, due to the nature of the topography (e.g. sea cliffs) and of much of the sequences (laterally variable shallow marine sandstone), and to the difficulties of aggregating thickness ranges given for components. All thicknesses below are from Morton (1965) except where indicated. In Trotternish, north Skye, including the type section, the formation ranges from 156 to 228m thick (see also Morton, 1976). On Strathaird [NG 52 11 to 56 21], it varies between 256 (Faoilean) and 488m (southern tip), and on Raasay attains up to about 214m. The succession at Glas Bheinn Beag [NG 585 257], near Dunan is approximately 235m. On Ardnamurchan, the formation is between 20m (British Geological Survey, 2009) and 37m (Richey and Thomas, 1930) thick. Strata attributed to the formation on southeast Mull total about 30m. Greater thicknesses might be present offshore (Fyfe et al., 1993)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BELL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.0.6m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BGL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "To 250m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BK> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Very variable, up to 160m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BRGP> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Averages c.900m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BRME> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "264m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BRYD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to 22m, but thins towards the margins of the outcrop."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BRYS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "80m at type section in south Pembrokshire."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BV> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "110m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BVYS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c 390m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BW> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "15.6 to 18.0m at Ravenscar, generally up to about 10m in Rosedale area, locally possibly up to 25m."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BYD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to about 12m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BYTH> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Individual aggradations are usually 3 to 5m thick; may total 18m locally."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CAVM> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Generally up to about 4m but in places up to about 13m thick"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CDF> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0-100m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CDI> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "To c.25m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CDL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "266m in the Avon Gorge at Bristol, thinning northwards to 137m north of Bristol and thinning southwards to 150-200m in the Mendip Hills."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CDM> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "60m at Bristol and northern Broadfield Down thinning to a feather edge on the southern side of Broadfield Down."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CFC> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "6m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CHSA> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Lower tongue: 6m at Chipping Sodbury to 43m at Cromhall. Middle tongue: 27m at Chipping Sodbury to 30m at Tytherington. Upper tongue: 18m on Broadfield Down thickening north to 240m at Cromhall."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CLQU> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Not known"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CLR> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "6 to 15m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CML> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to c.2m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CSA> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "469-529m in Sellafield boreholes"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CSMG> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "<1m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CVO> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to c.10m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CWSG> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Probably up to about 7m, but only 4.3m at type section."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/DARL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to 350m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/DGR> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Variable, both locally and regionally; generally about 0.75 to 2m thick on the Yorkshire Coast and in ferruginous sandstone/ironstone lithofacies; limestone and mudstone lithofacies, up to 12.2m locally preserved. Thought locally to attain 29 m in the Rosedale area [SE 729 946] (Hemingway, 1974, p. 188), although Young, T P (1994) regards much of this strata as belonging to the underlying Blea Wyke Sandstone Formation in which case the Dogger Formation here is up to about 8 m thick. May be absent, locally,  due to erosion prior to deposition of the overlying Saltwick Formation (Ravenscar Group)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/DOBP> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to more than 10m - maximum thickness unknown"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ELL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to c.1m."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ERIS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to 1.6m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/FHAM> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Generally up to about 4m but a borehole at [TL 8504 6747] proved 5.6m. BGS Borehole Registration No.TL86NE/101."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/FOGR> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to about 3m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/FRCR> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to 160m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/GCO> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "15m in the Bristol area [Avon Gorge] thickening to 70m at Weston-super-Mare."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/GWO> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "10m in the Clydach Gorge to 20m on the east crop."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HBL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "17m at type locality in southwest Pembrokeshire."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HGV> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to about 15m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HIL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.6 to 13m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HLG> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "At least 30m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HLSI> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.5m (Cook et al. p59-69 in Lewis et al.,1991)"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HMR> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "To c.25m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HMSF> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "61m (Clarkly Hill No. 1 Borehole [NJ 1270 6833]) to 70m +"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HNRD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to c.8m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HOTI> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to 10m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HOWH> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Probably in excess of 10m, but information is lacking."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HURD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "About 2m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HWCL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "2 to 3m in type area, 1.2m at Lamb and Flag Quarry, c.3.7m at Wootton Bassett."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HWGR> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "2 to 3m in the type area, 1.2m at Lamb and Flag Quarry, c.3.7m at Westbury and Wootton Bassett."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HWLS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "2 to 3m in type area, 2.6m at Lamb and Flag Quarry, thins laterally, 0.3m at Wooton Bassett."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ISAG> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.13.2m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KCM> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to c.9.5m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KCMK> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to 5m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KFRD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Generally up to about 4m but in places for example at [TL 706 634] the deposits are at least 6m thick."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KKF> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.4500m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KKMB> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0.15m in type section"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KLB> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to perhaps (in south Dorset) 50m; typically c.20m in the Wessex Basin, and c.5 to 8m on the East Midlands Shelf."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KLC> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to perhaps (in south Dorset) c.50m; typically c.20m in the Wessex Basin, and 2 to 3m on the East Midlands Shelf."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KLS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to c.10m; typically c.3 to 5m on the East Midland Shelf; thin or absent over much of Dorset."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LCB> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to c.4m; typically c.3m. Absent north of Peterborough."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LFRD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Generally up to between about 4 and 5m but locally over 9m thick."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LGFL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "1.0 to 3.5m; 1.39m in type section."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LHTH> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to about 3m."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0-30m (south Lincolneshire) or more (see Ashton, 1980)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LLL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to c.20m (south Lincolnshire)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LOFT> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Extremely variable. It is thickest in buried valleys where locally up to 60m may be present. Thick accumulations are also more generally present beneath much of northern Essex and south Suffolk."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LRL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.300m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LTGL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0.2 to 1.5m; c1.5m in type section."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LTGP> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.670m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MLLL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to 1.1m; 1.07m in type section."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MMS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.200m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MODS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "82m+"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MPMU> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 - 19m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MW> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Unknown in detail, 500 to1200m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NACL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to 10m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NP> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Generally less than 1m, but locally up to over 3m where preserved in channels."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NRD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "c.26m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/OULT> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Maximum thickness of 2.2m observed at stratotype."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PABS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "200m maximum"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PEE> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "2m+"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PET2> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Unknown probably less than 5m."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PET3> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Unknown probably less than 5m."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PET5> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Unknown, probably less than 5m."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to c.100m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PVL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "500m +"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PYF> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "To 6m in the type area."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RDDI> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "0 to 4.5m (Swindon-Faringdon area); 0-1.5m (Lyneham area)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RDSG> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Of very variable thickness, generally less than 5m, but potentially greater in the Hunstanton Esker."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RHP> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "At least 257m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RVB> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "Up to c.8m"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SBNB> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasThicknessDescription> "3 to 5m; c 4.0m in type section."@en .
