-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HERN> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Limestone and mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Turonian Age (Cretaceous Period) (93.9-89.4 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HIDR> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Limestone and mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Cenomanian Age (Cretaceous Period) (100.5-93.9 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HMSF> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Sandstone with subsidiary pebbly (gravelly) sandstone and siliciclastic argillaceous rock and trace siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs both onshore and offshore. Deposited during the Guadalupian Epoch (Permian Period) - to - Early Triassic Epoch (Triassic Period) (274.4-246.7 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HOTI> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Clay, diamicton and silt. Stratified superficial deposits. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Devensian Stage (Quaternary Period) (.116-.0118 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HSTMB> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Duckmantian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (318-314.75 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HYMB> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Shelly mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Duckmantian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (318-314.75 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/INCA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Dolostone with subsidiary limestone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Guadalupian Epoch - to - Lopingian Epoch (Permian Period) (274.4-251.9 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/INVO> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Basalt and tuff with subsidiary mudstone and tuffaceous-mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Cisuralian Epoch (Permian Period) (298.9-274.4 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/IRAN> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Anhydrite-stone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Guadalupian Epoch - to - Lopingian Epoch (Permian Period) (274.4-251.9 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/JOMU> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Mudstone with subsidiary sandstone and trace dolostone and limestone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Carnian Age - to - Norian Age (Triassic Period) (237-205.7 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/JOSA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Mudstone, sandstone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Ladinian Age - to - Carnian Age (Triassic Period) (241.5-227.3 Ma BP)."@en .
