-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SDWC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Coal. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Duckmantian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (318-314.75 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SEVN> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Gravel and sand with subsidiary clay, peat and silt. Stratified superficial deposits. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Pleistocene Epoch - to - Holocene Epoch (Quaternary Period) (2.58-0 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SGGT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Bedrock. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Arnsbergian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (327-323.75 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SGMB> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Langsettian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (319-318 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SHWT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Halite-stone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Guadalupian Epoch - to - Lopingian Epoch (Permian Period) (274.4-251.9 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SKAV> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Gravelly sand with subsidiary clayey silt. Stratified superficial deposits. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Quaternary Period (2.58-0 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SM> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Bedrock. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Pendleian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (330.3-327 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SMBA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Mudstone with subsidiary siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Early Triassic Epoch - to - Anisian Age (Triassic Period) (251.9-241.5 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SOARV> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Gravel and sand with subsidiary clay and silt. Stratified superficial deposits. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Pleistocene Epoch - to - Holocene Epoch (Quaternary Period) (2.58-0 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SOYSG> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Gravel and sand with subsidiary peat and silt. Stratified superficial deposits. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Pleistocene Epoch (Quaternary Period) (2.58-.0118 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SPEK> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Mudstone, sandstone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Early Jurassic Epoch (Jurassic Period) (201.4-174.7 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SSTMB> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Langsettian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (319-318 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ST> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Andesite and tuff. Bedrock. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Neoproterozoic Era (Precambrian) (1000-541 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/STGMB> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Duckmantian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (318-314.75 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/STIE> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Conglomerate with subsidiary mudstone, sandstone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Early Devonian Epoch (Devonian Period) (419-394.3 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/STLN> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Cenomanian Age - to - Maastrichtian Age (Cretaceous Period) (100.5-66 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/STPS> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Bedrock. Occurs onshore. Formed during the Frasnian Age (Devonian Period) (378.9-371.1 Ma BP)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/STRR> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Conglomerate and sandstone with subsidiary mudstone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Eifelian Age - to - Givetian Age (Devonian Period) (394.3-378.9 Ma BP)."@en .
